snippet.title: U.S. National Park Service- Archeology
snippet.description: This page serves as the index page for a series of documents that provide an OVERVIEW of the prehistory of Alaska and for another set of documents that briefly describe the cultural resources (Archeology, history, ethnography) in each national park and preserve in the state.

snippet.title: The State of Alaska - An Introduction to the Last Frontier from NETSTATE.COM
snippet.description: America's last frontier! Alaska, admitted as the 49th state to the union is thought of as "America's Last Frontier" because of its distance from the lower 48 states and because of its rugged landscape and climate.
